snippet.textDisplay: i don’t know if anyone else noticed the “on the other side” reference at the end. julian went from “nobody’s waiting for me on the other side” to “i know you’re waiting for me on the other side” to “i’ll be waiting from the other side, waiting for the tide to rise” like holy shit. on the other side is my favorite record by the strokes, but you can really feel the pain through that track, much like you can on this song. outro references like, especially to such a self-loathing song, mean more than they appear. fucking amazing track man, but dude’s been going through a lot in recent times. hope he’s okay and has people checking on him

snippet.textDisplay:
The video is incredible, I've seen it several times and every time I find something more related to another.

I feel that the video tries to tell the story of a person in his death (2:20), that the first thing he sees is the death that hugs him and makes him see something. Where he returns us to the past as a child, where he lives a bad experience (0:20). Something interesting is that the rabbit in the video is himself (you can see it in his eyes) and the bad rabbit is the bad memory and leaves a scar in his past (1:46).

The cinematic of the super hero tries to show how he tries to overcome this last moment and accept it (3:50), death is the one who helps him remember the past, of course (2:47).

In the end he leaves everything behind. (4:44)
